OL,7,FFor six years she suffered crippling
OL,8,Fdepression, the last three years of
OL,9,Fwhich she spent in the care of doctors
OL,10,Fand psychiatrists, convincing them
OL,11,Fthat her pain was unbearable and her
OL,12,Fdesire to die irreversible.
OL,14,FDirk and Karin came to accept their
OL,15,Fdaughter's wishes and were with her in
OL,16,Fthe room when she died. "To be honest
OL,17,Feuthanasia was a much better option
OL,18,Fthan she go under a train or
OL,19,Fsomething", Karin told me.
