OL,7,FThey both agreed that for her the
OL,8,Fhappiest moment of that entire six
OL,9,Fyears was when she woke up on the day
OL,10,Fof her appointment and headed to the
OL,11,Fclinic for a final time.
OL,13,F"As a parent we could have asked her
OL,14,Fto keep living to make us happy, but
OL,15,Fus being happy wouldn't have made her
OL,16,Fhappy" said her father. "At one point
OL,17,FI had said to Elien "If I had two
OL,18,Fmedicines, one of which could make you
OL,19,Fbetter and the other make you die,
OL,20,Fwhich one would you choose? And she
OL,21,Fsaid the one that would kill her".
