OL,3,CBelgium's 'slippery slope' for
OL,4,Cassisted dying laws could provide
OL,5,Cexample for UK
OL,7,FHe points out, as an example, the
OL,8,Fright not to be discriminated against.
OL,9,F"Why would it be legal for someone to
OL,10,Fbe allowed to end their life for the
OL,11,Funbearable pain of a physical illness,
OL,12,Fbut not for a mental one. You must be
OL,13,Faware that if you want one you will
OL,14,Fget the other. Inevitably," he says.
OL,16,FOriginally, explains Keuleneer, the
OL,17,Flegislation simply decriminalised
OL,18,Fmedical euthanasia, but that quickly
OL,19,Fbecame a right to euthanasia. "It
OL,20,Fdeveloped very fast from being a last
OL,21,Fresort to the first question," he says.
